remixlab.proscene

Class GenericModelObject<E extends Enum<E>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • remixlab.proscene.GenericModelObject<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - Reference action used to parameterize the GenericModel
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    GenericGrabber<E>, Grabber, GenericModel<E>, Model

    public abstract class GenericModelObject<E extends Enum<E>>
extends Object
implements GenericModel<E>
    GenericModel object which eases third-party implementation of the GenericModel interface.

    Based on the concrete event type, this model object splits the performInteraction(BogusEvent) method into more specific versions of it, e.g., performInteraction(DOF6Event), performInteraction(KeyboardEvent) and so on. Thus allowing implementations of this abstract InteractiveModelObject to override only those method signatures that might be of their interest.

    This interactive model object implementation also provided an algorithm to parse an Action sequence from an init action variable, see processEvent(BogusEvent).

        An interactive-model-object is selected using 'ray-picking' with a color buffer (see Scene.pickingBuffer()). This method compares the color of the Scene.pickingBuffer() at (x,y) with getColor(). Returns true if both colors are the same, and false otherwise.

      • addGraphicsHandler

        public void addGraphicsHandler(Object obj,
                               String methodName)
        Attempt to add a graphics handler method to the InteractiveFrame. The default event handler is a method that returns void and has one single PGraphics parameter. Note that the method should only deal with geometry and that not coloring procedure may be specified within it.
        Parameters:
        obj - the object to handle the event
        methodName - the method to execute in the object handler class
        See Also:
        removeGraphicsHandler(), invokeGraphicsHandler(PGraphics)
